TY  - JOUR
T1  - Generalizability of the Vertical Dyad Linkage Model of Leadership
AU  - Liden, Robert C.
AU  - Graen, George
Y1  - 1980/09/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255511
DO  - 10.5465/255511
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 451
EP  - 465
VL  - 23
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The validity of the Vertical Dyad Linkage model of leadership was tested under conditions differing substantially from those investigated in past research on the model. In over 90 percent of the units in this study, supervisors formed different quality relationships with their subordinates. Subordinates reporting high quality relationships with their supervisors assumed greater job responsibility, contributed more to their units, and were rated as higher performers than those reporting low quality relationships.
AB  - The validity of the Vertical Dyad Linkage model of leadership was tested under conditions differing substantially from those investigated in past research on the model. In over 90 percent of the units in this study, supervisors formed different quality relationships with their subordinates. Subordinates reporting high quality relationships with their supervisors assumed greater job responsibility, contributed more to their units, and were rated as higher performers than those reporting low quality relationships.
